        "created_at": "2023-01-09T17:47:58.965Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi folks!</p>\n<p>The following Python script doesn\u2019t trigger the transaction timeout on a pending watch operation. Am I doing something wrong?</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">import fdb\nfdb.api_version(710)\ndb = fdb.open()\ndb.set(fdb.tuple.pack((1,)), fdb.tuple.pack((2,)))\ntr = db.create_transaction()\ntr.options.set_timeout(1000)\ntr.watch(fdb.tuple.pack((1,))).wait()\n</code></pre>\n<p>I would expect the transaction to timeout after one second. What am I doing wrong?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2023-01-10T14:19:18.135Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
